<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A3E3BBBCFF6FF2E4" bold="true" box="[136,186,198,219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">
<typeStatus id="C67B8809FF99FFF8A3E3BBBCFF6FF2E4" box="[136,186,198,219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Type</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
(designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="7D514B5AFF99FFF8A238BBBCFD9BF2E3" author="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N." box="[339,590,198,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" refId="ref7972" refString="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N. (1922) The Cactaceae. Descriptions and Illustrations of Plants of the Cactus Family, vols. 3 - 4 Carnegie Institution, Washington, 322 pp." type="book" year="1922">Britton &amp; Rose 1922: 210</bibRefCitation>
):— 
<taxonomicName id="DEC04D28FF99FFF8A118BBBCFC00F2E4" authority="Britton &amp; Rose." authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose." box="[627,981,198,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cataphracta">
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A118BBBCFCE0F2E4" box="[627,821,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Frailea cataphracta</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="197F36ABFF99FFF8A3E3BA70FD7FF377" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A3E3BA70FEBBF31B" bold="true" box="[136,366,266,292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Species richness:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DEC04D28FF99FFF8A205BA70FE17F31B" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1922" box="[366,450,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A205BA70FE17F31B" box="[366,450,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Frailea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 19 species according to 
<bibRefCitation id="7D514B5AFF99FFF8A038BA70FC2FF31B" author="Gerloff, N." box="[851,1018,266,292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" pagination="138 - 147" refId="ref8364" refString="Gerloff, N. (2001) Frailea densispina (Hofacker &amp; Herm) N. Gerloff, Comb. &amp; Stat. Nov. Cactus &amp; Co 3 (5): 138 - 147." type="journal article" year="2001">Gerloff (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. Twelve are endemic, recognized only for 
<collectingRegion id="DB04F849FF99FFF8A3DBBA54FE15F377" box="[176,448,302,328]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Rio Grande do Sul State</collectingRegion>
(Pontes 
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A149BA55FD8FF377" box="[546,602,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">et al.</emphasis>
2018).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="197F36ABFF99FFF8A3D6BA28FD5BF3AF" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A3D6BA28FE02F353" bold="true" box="[189,471,338,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">General distribution:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DEC04D28FF99FFF8A2BCBA28FDFEF353" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1922" box="[471,555,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A2BCBA28FDFEF353" box="[471,555,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Frailea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted geographical distribution to southern 
<collectingCountry id="61D7763BFF99FFF8A714BA28FB13F353" box="[1151,1222,338,364]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="61D7763BFF99FFF8A7BABA29FAEFF352" box="[1233,1338,339,365]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="61D7763BFF99FFF8A62FBA29FA72F352" box="[1348,1447,339,365]" name="Uruguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="61D7763BFF99FFF8A270BA0CFEA5F3AF" box="[283,368,374,400]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, and northeast 
<collectingCountry id="61D7763BFF99FFF8A17CBA0CFD5FF3AF" box="[535,650,374,400]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="51DA6520FF99FFF7A3D6BAE0FD1CF31B" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="161" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="197F36ABFF99FFF8A3D6BAE0FCDEF07A" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis id="2BB4EAB9FF99FFF8A3D6BAE0FD6AF38B" bold="true" box="[189,703,410,436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Distribution in Santa Maria river basin:—</emphasis>
In SMRB occur nine species, 
<taxonomicName id="DEC04D28FF99FFF8A77EBAE0FB0DF38B" box="[1045,1240,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albifusca">
